sgn(t)
 sgn(t) = \begin{cases} 1, & t > 0 \\ 0, & t = 0 \\ -1, & t < 0. \end{cases} 
 X(\omega) = \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} sgn(t) e^{-i\omega t} \, dt = \int_0^{\infty} e^{-i\omega t} \, dt + \int_{-\infty}^0 -e^{-i\omega t} \, dt. 
f(x) = 1
f(x) = \delta(x)
 \operatorname{sgn}(t) = -1 + 2\int_{-\infty}^t \delta(\tau)\,d\tau 
